## üîò 4. Button Colors

Buttons use the accent color automatically. To customize:

### Method 1: Change Accent Color (Easiest)
```css
--accent: 270 70% 50%;  /* Changes all buttons to purple */
```

### Method 2: Custom Button Styles

Create custom button in [index.css](file:///c:/Users/Purvil/Desktop/Projects/Social%20Agency/Demo-clickboost-media-project/src/index.css) (add after line 178):

```css
.btn-custom {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #FF6B6B 0%, #FF8E53 100%);
  color: white;
  padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
  border-radius: 0.5rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  transition: all 0.3s;
}

.btn-custom:hover {
  transform: translateY(-2px);
  box-shadow: 0 10px 25px rgba(255, 107, 107, 0.3);
}
```

**Use in components:**
```tsx
<button className="btn-custom">Custom Button</button>
```

